-- Akbank Drops for 6th Day in Istanbul on Citigroup Disposal
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-28T14:55:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/akbank-drops-for-6th-day-in-istanbul-on-citigroup-disposal-1-.html
Akbank TAS (AKBNK) , the Turkish bank part-
owned by  Citigroup Inc. (C) , dropped for a sixth day after the U.S.
lender reduced its stake by more than half last week.  The shares dropped 2.2 percent to 5.32 liras at the close
in Istanbul, the lowest since July 2009.  Citigroup sold 404 million shares in Akbank, or a 10.1
percent stake, for 5.24 liras each, it said in a statement last
week. Citigroup will retain its remaining 9.9 percent stake in
Akbank for three years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
